        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-10T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="780" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–1045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-10T15:00:00-05:00">December 10, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1965. Chungking report appearing Dec 9 papers here states <hi rend="italic">inter
                        alia</hi> that Chinese have obtained Russian permission to occupy Harbin,
                    Changchun and Dairen.</p>
                <p>Please investigate and report urgently.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
